    <section class="panel hero">
      <div class="kicker">
        <span class="tag">CEO BRIEF</span>
        <span class="tag">DEFENCE / INDUSTRIAL GOVERNANCE</span>
        <span class="tag">NO AI • DETERMINISTIC • AUDITABLE</span>
      </div>

      <h1>
        Decisions will be challenged. <span class="gold">Make them reconstructible.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="lead">
        In large defence-grade organizations, the risk is rarely the decision itself.
        The risk is <span class="gold">being unable to reconstruct</span> what data existed, what perimeter was considered,
        what constraints applied, and why the decision was defensible at that moment.
        <br><br>
        OpenProof RPO v0.1 is a minimal proof layer: it produces a deterministic bundle (sealed JSON + human-readable preview + public hash)
        that can be verified later — without rewriting history, and without delegating judgment to AI.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-grid">
        <!-- Left: CEO framing -->
        <div class="card">
          <h3>What this fixes (CEO-level)</h3>
          <ul class="bullets">
            <li><strong>Audit & investigations:</strong> reconstructable decision trails (what, when, with what data, under which constraints).</li>
            <li><strong>Industrial accountability:</strong> defendable governance across multi-entities, programs, sites, and chains of command.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal & compliance exposure:</strong> integrity guarantees for evidence bundles (tamper-evident, reproducible).</li>
            <li><strong>Operational trust:</strong> a shared language between HR, Security, Legal, IT, Compliance, and Exec.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="hr"></div>

          <p class="mini">
            Think of it as a <strong>flight recorder for decisions</strong>:
            it does not fly the aircraft; it makes the trajectory verifiable after turbulence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: cockpit snapshot -->
        <div class="card cockpit" aria-label="Cockpit preview">
          <h3>Decision defensibility snapshot</h3>

          <div class="metric">
            <div>
              <div class="label">Coverage</div>
